description:
Add a custom CSS `sorting` class for table headings that uses a moderate font weight, and apply the same styling to sidebar labels instead of bold (`<b>`) tags.

## CSS
```css
.sorting { color: #333; font-weight: 600 !important; font-size: 1em; }
.sorting_asc { color: #333; font-weight: 600 !important; font-size: 1em; }
.sorting_desc { color: #333; font-weight: 600 !important; font-size: 1em; }
```

Replace `<b>` tags in slide-out labels with the sorting class for visual consistency.
